text: The Boeing International Headquarters (colloquially known as the Boeing Building and formerly known as the Morton International Building) is a 36-floor skyscraper located in the Near West Side of Chicago. The building has been made the corporate headquarters for Boeing, which decided in 2001 to move to Chicago from Seattle.Wallace, James. "Boeing picks Chicago; will move by Sept. 4." Seattle Post-Intelligencer. Thursday May 10, 2001.
